column4: 5 Black Writers You Should Read, Know and Study
column6: These authors were eons ahead of their time in who and what they wrote about, in their imaginations, and in their politics. They spoke their truth through fiction, which is why their work resonates with me so much. They were most active in the 20th century and, as of last year, they are all among our ancestors.

column4: Alice Walker Interview: Joining Civil Rights Movement and creating the color Purple
column6: Alice Walker recalls the influence of both her parents, being the youngest of 8 children, her family facing racism, how she fell in love with art at a young age, immediately joining the Civil Rights Movement when she got to college, and starting her first book while living in Africa. Walker discusses how her 10th and most popular book, The Color Purple was inspired by stories from her Grandparents and why she was determined to have people understand their voices.
